# Trivy ignore file — consumed by the CI "Scan app image (Trivy)" gate
# (.github/workflows/ci.yml). One CVE ID per line. Every entry MUST carry a
# justification and a re-review trigger. Do NOT add blanket ignores here to
# silence the gate — fix (bump the dep) unless there is a documented reason.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# starlette (pinned transitively by fastapi==0.104.1 -> starlette==0.27.0).
# The real Linux-exploitable multipart DoS (CVE-2024-47874) is NOT ignored —
# it is cleared by bumping to starlette>=0.40 when fastapi is upgraded.
# The two below require starlette 1.1.0 / 1.3.1, which no fastapi release in
# the 0.10x–0.12x line adopts, so they cannot be cleared without a bleeding-
# edge fastapi + pydantic>=2.7 jump. Both are low-risk on this stack:
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# SSRF / NTLM credential theft via UNC paths in StaticFiles. UNC paths are a
# Windows-only construct; this backend runs on Debian containers, so the code
# path is not reachable. Re-review if the app is ever run on Windows.
CVE-2026-48818

# request.form() size limits silently ignored for application/x-www-form-
# urlencoded bodies -> DoS. Low severity; already mitigated by the per-client
# rate limiter (app/core/limiter.py). Drop this entry when fastapi is bumped
# to a release that pins starlette>=1.3.1.
CVE-2026-54283
